<symsect><title>Symbol Definition</title>
<para>The following list of symbols are used in this manual and adhere
to requirements of DoD specification MIL-STD-38784.</para>
<symtitle>List of Symbols</symtitle>
<term><esds></term><def>This is the symbol used to indicate Electrostatic
Discharge Sensitive parts. ESDS parts require to be handled in accordance
with the ESDS device handling procedures in TO 00-25-234.  This explanation
shall be preceded by a CAUTION heading.</def>
<term>**HCI**</term><def>This is the symbol used for a Harness Critical
Item. This shall include an explanation that the HCI symbol establishes
special requirements limiting changes and substitutions, and that
the specific parts listed must be used to ensure hardness is not degraded.
 This statement shall be preceded by a CAUTION heading.</def>
<term><esds></term><def>This is the symbol used to indicate Electrostatic
Discharge Sensitive parts. ESDS parts require to be handled in accordance
