<applicdef><title>List of Applicability and Effectivity</title>
<para>In this example the &ldquo;TERM&rdquo; heading is used to define
the column used for the symbol.<acronym><def>Alphabet Soup. Let&rsquo;s
make this one really long so we can see what happens when the definition
wraps to another line. It should indent and align under the definition
column.</def><term>ABC</term></acronym> The &ldquo;DEFINITION&rdquo;
heading is used to define the applicability/effectivity for the symbol
used in the &ldquo;TERM&rdquo; column.</para>
<applichd>
<term>TERM</term><def>DEFINITION</def>
</applichd>
<applic id="e">
<term>e</term><def>This is applicability a. <acronym><def>Air Force
Base</def><term>AFB</term></acronym>This could also contain a listing
of serial numbers as for an aircraft or to define applicability to
a part number.<acronym><def>Air Force Base</def><term>AFB</term>
</acronym></def>
</applic>
<applic id="f">
<term>f</term><def>This is applicability b. This could also contain
a listing of serial numbers as for an aircraft or to define applicability
to a part number.</def>
</applic>
<applic id="g">
<term>g</term><def>This is applicability c. This could also contain
a listing of serial numbers as for an aircraft or to define applicability
to a part number.</def>
</applic>
